WEBVTT

00:02.419 --> 00:04.588
Good morning!
Maya:
Let's go! Everybody up!

00:04.588 --> 00:06.798
What's going on?
It's 3:00 a. m.!

00:06.798 --> 00:08.342
Is it an earthquake?

00:08.342 --> 00:09.801
Yes! We finally get to eat
the emergency tuna fish.

00:09.801 --> 00:11.178
It's moving day.

00:11.178 --> 00:12.721
We realized we've got
to get all of our stuff

00:12.721 --> 00:14.139
out of the old house
by 7:00 a. m.

00:14.139 --> 00:15.182
Yay!

00:15.182 --> 00:17.267
Coming through.
Why are you saying "yay"?

00:17.267 --> 00:19.520
To make it sound fun.
Didn't work. Moving on.

00:19.520 --> 00:21.355
How did you forget about this
until now?

00:21.355 --> 00:23.190
Oh, Ray,
if your dad and I planned,

00:23.190 --> 00:24.107
you wouldn't be here
at all.

00:24.107 --> 00:25.651
Not you.
I wanted you.

00:25.651 --> 00:27.402
Ray, everybody's ready.
Let's go.
No.

00:27.402 --> 00:28.946
I refuse to get up
on principle

00:28.946 --> 00:30.280
because this is
so disorganized.

00:30.280 --> 00:32.699
[ Sighs ]

00:32.699 --> 00:34.993
Why the hell
are you naked?
I was
trying something out!

00:38.997 --> 00:40.582
Jimmy: Two hours.

00:40.582 --> 00:43.126
Grab anything you want
to take to the new house.

00:43.126 --> 00:44.711
Found the moving shovels!

00:44.711 --> 00:47.589
Can I make a suggestion
to save us all a ton of time?

00:47.589 --> 00:49.800
And doesn't use JJ
as a snowplow?

00:49.800 --> 00:51.551
Oh, he's having
the time of his life.

00:51.551 --> 00:53.971
Go on, love.
You're almost through.

00:53.971 --> 00:55.389
Let's not take this stuff,
any of it.

00:55.389 --> 00:56.348
But it's our stuff.

00:56.348 --> 00:58.267
Yes, but before
it was our stuff,

00:58.267 --> 00:59.810
it was
other people's garbage.

00:59.810 --> 01:03.105
The chair we found under
a bridge, and the fish tank...

01:03.105 --> 01:04.856
That is a perfectly good
TV stand.

01:04.856 --> 01:06.316
No, it is not!

01:06.316 --> 01:08.610
Nor was it a perfectly good
"Dylan's crib."

01:08.610 --> 01:11.321
Remember when she used to pound
her little fists on the glass.

01:11.321 --> 01:12.114
"Help!"

01:12.114 --> 01:14.074
Ray,
these are our things,

01:14.074 --> 01:17.494
and there's a certain romance
to how we got them ‐‐

01:17.494 --> 01:20.414
the thrill of the chase,
the excitement of the big score.

01:20.414 --> 01:21.790
It's like hunting,

01:21.790 --> 01:23.208
but you don't have to pretend
you like deer meat.

01:23.208 --> 01:24.293
Wouldn't you love a house

01:24.293 --> 01:26.295
with nice things
that go well together?

01:26.295 --> 01:28.922
A room with a tasteful rug
and matching lamps?

01:28.922 --> 01:30.591
This is embarrassing.

01:30.591 --> 01:33.385
I'm sorry you feel that way
about our life, Ray,

01:33.385 --> 01:36.054
but we have challenges
other families don't.

01:36.054 --> 01:37.764
You use that excuse
for everything.

01:37.764 --> 01:40.601
I'm sorry I don't have other,
better excuses, Ray,

01:40.601 --> 01:42.853
but we have challenges
other families don't.

01:42.853 --> 01:43.895
[ Wheelchair motor whirs,
crashing ]

01:43.895 --> 01:45.147
Yes!

01:45.147 --> 01:47.149
I knew you could do it,
darling!

01:47.149 --> 01:49.234
♪♪

01:49.234 --> 01:52.029
Hey, hey!
Look at you, baby girl.

01:52.029 --> 01:54.656
You sure like that running,
don't you?

01:54.656 --> 01:57.409
Yeah, yeah, yeah, yeah,
yeah, yeah, yeah, I get it.

01:57.409 --> 01:58.869
What's that
supposed to mean?

01:58.869 --> 02:00.120
Well, it's funny.

02:00.120 --> 02:02.497
Your brother doesn't walk,
so to compensate,

02:02.497 --> 02:04.541
you push yourself
to run as fast as you can.

02:04.541 --> 02:06.668
It's like you're running
for the both of you.

02:06.668 --> 02:08.879
Is that why I run?

02:08.879 --> 02:10.422
I thought I liked it.

02:10.422 --> 02:13.467
Eh, I dunno.
That's one theory.

02:13.467 --> 02:15.093
Well, enjoy your run.

02:15.093 --> 02:16.136
Meep‐meep!

02:16.136 --> 02:18.889
♪♪

02:18.889 --> 02:21.308
What am I running <i>from?</i>

02:21.308 --> 02:23.352
Good morning, DiMeos!

02:23.352 --> 02:25.854
What's all this stuff?
What's going on in here?

02:25.854 --> 02:27.606
JJ has special needs.

02:27.606 --> 02:29.733
It's also why we're eating
licorice for breakfast.

02:29.733 --> 02:33.236
You tell them about school,
hot shot?

02:33.236 --> 02:35.489
"I made some friends."

02:35.489 --> 02:37.366
Not just friends ‐‐
cool friends.

02:37.366 --> 02:39.368
Tell them
what we did yesterday.

02:39.368 --> 02:41.787
"We pranked Eastlake."

02:41.787 --> 02:43.622
Well,
it's Homecoming Week,

02:43.622 --> 02:46.124
so Lafayette and Eastlake High
have this prank war.

02:46.124 --> 02:48.543
Frickin' epic!

02:48.543 --> 02:50.671
If you're in high school.
Yeah, I find it silly.

02:50.671 --> 02:53.715
"Show the video."

02:53.715 --> 02:56.927
Oh, yeah, yeah,
yeah, yeah. Oh, okay.

02:56.927 --> 02:58.095
Here we are.

02:58.095 --> 02:59.221
Boy:
<i>You ready to go, JJ?</i>

02:59.221 --> 03:01.640
So, there's Dan Holden,
total stud.

03:01.640 --> 03:03.975
And Zach Garcia ‐‐ he's the
captain of the football team,

03:03.975 --> 03:05.519
but he's
super down‐to‐earth.

03:05.519 --> 03:07.437
Okay, so, now, originally,
we were gonna

03:07.437 --> 03:09.648
tie up their quarterback
and send him up the flag pole,

03:09.648 --> 03:11.525
but Rob White's
a lock for Stanford,

03:11.525 --> 03:13.443
and you don't want to
mess with that.

03:13.443 --> 03:15.028
Stop saying
teenagers' names.

03:15.028 --> 03:17.155
<i>All right, JJ, pull it up.</i>

03:17.155 --> 03:18.573
<i>Do the honors, JJ.</i>

03:18.573 --> 03:21.034
<i>Hey! Yeah!</i>

03:21.034 --> 03:22.869
[ <i>Laughter</i> ]

03:22.869 --> 03:25.372
JJ, look at you!

03:25.372 --> 03:28.250
And the doctors said you'd never
be able to commit vandalism.

03:28.250 --> 03:29.918
Do you know, putting you
in a mainstream school

03:29.918 --> 03:31.420
was the best decision
we ever made.

03:31.420 --> 03:35.173
You're being included.
And you're cool!

03:35.173 --> 03:37.217
I know a mother's not allowed
to say that matters,

03:37.217 --> 03:39.761
but now that we're being honest,
it's all that matters!

03:39.761 --> 03:41.263
It is?

03:41.263 --> 03:43.557
Oh, darling, this opens up
whole new worlds.

03:43.557 --> 03:46.393
You're gonna need new clothes,
maybe a motorcycle...

03:46.393 --> 03:49.146
Don't go getting
any young ladies pregnant.

03:49.146 --> 03:50.272
Yeah, like Allen Rice!

03:50.272 --> 03:52.149
Dude's a sophomore,
but he's all,

03:52.149 --> 03:55.026
"Oh, I got to go pick up my kid
at preschool."

03:57.237 --> 03:59.489
It's more sad
than anything.

03:59.489 --> 04:02.826
♪♪

04:02.826 --> 04:04.786
I was a runner once.

04:04.786 --> 04:07.664
Who broke the kid?

04:07.664 --> 04:11.460
I‐G‐H‐T.

04:11.460 --> 04:12.794
"And that's what your mom
told me last night"?

04:12.794 --> 04:15.589
[ Laughter ]

04:15.589 --> 04:17.799
Hey, guys!
Bonfire tickets.

04:17.799 --> 04:20.385
It's the Homecoming Bonfire
tomorrow night.

04:20.385 --> 04:22.262
All the upperclassmen
get to go.

04:22.262 --> 04:23.680
There are teacher chaperones,
but, like,

04:23.680 --> 04:25.140
the younger teachers
who let us drink

04:25.140 --> 04:26.433
because they want to be
friends with us.

04:26.433 --> 04:29.102
[ Scoffs ]
How lame! Am I right?

04:29.102 --> 04:30.520
Huh?

04:30.520 --> 04:31.897
No?

04:34.232 --> 04:35.859
It's at,
uh, Dragon's Cove.

04:35.859 --> 04:36.943
Um...

04:36.943 --> 04:38.361
Getting there's
half the fun.

04:38.361 --> 04:40.489
You got to, like, jump up
this rock thing,

04:40.489 --> 04:43.241
then shimmy through
this crevasse, and, um...

04:43.241 --> 04:44.326
Oh, man.

04:44.326 --> 04:46.661
You're not much of
a shimmy guy, are you?

04:46.661 --> 04:48.079
Crap. JJ can't come.

04:48.079 --> 04:49.915
That sucks.

04:49.915 --> 04:52.292
That sucks!

04:52.292 --> 04:54.252
"It's all good."

04:54.252 --> 04:55.504
You sure, man?

04:55.504 --> 04:57.297
"I'll just chill at home...

04:57.297 --> 04:58.799
with your moms."

04:58.799 --> 05:01.009
Whoa!
[ Laughter ]

05:01.009 --> 05:02.677
Dude...
[ School bell rings ]

05:02.677 --> 05:06.473
[ Laughs ]

05:06.473 --> 05:07.933
I hope your boyfriend's
not threatened

05:07.933 --> 05:08.767
that we're walking
together.

05:08.767 --> 05:11.144
[ Laughs ]

05:11.144 --> 05:13.772
That's a...
hearty laugh.

05:13.772 --> 05:16.566
Oh, Sandeep said you have
a model of the Jupiter probe?

05:16.566 --> 05:17.359
Is that true?

05:17.359 --> 05:19.861
Ugh.
Sandeep is such a gossip.

05:19.861 --> 05:21.363
Yes, it's true.

05:21.363 --> 05:22.405
Can I see it?

05:22.405 --> 05:23.490
Really?

05:23.490 --> 05:24.866
Jimmy:
Ah, Ray, come here!

05:24.866 --> 05:27.994
Help me
with this soda bottle!

05:27.994 --> 05:29.579
You know
what would be simpler?

05:29.579 --> 05:31.581
Let's meet up downtown
in an hour.

05:31.581 --> 05:33.333
I'll show you the probe
there.

05:33.333 --> 05:35.168
Uh...
I think I'll just go home.

05:35.168 --> 05:37.546
Great.

05:37.546 --> 05:39.297
But this went
really well.

05:39.297 --> 05:42.551
I think
that's the takeaway!

05:42.551 --> 05:43.635
[ Sighs ]

05:47.347 --> 05:49.850
Oh, look who's home
from school.

05:49.850 --> 05:51.726
Coolest thing on wheels.

05:51.726 --> 05:54.563
I got you something.

05:54.563 --> 05:55.730
I made it.

05:55.730 --> 05:57.649
New board for a new life.

05:57.649 --> 05:59.526
I figured you might want to
pepper in some cooler phrases,

05:59.526 --> 06:02.237
so new offerings include,
"'Sup?"

06:02.237 --> 06:04.197
"Hey, Girl," and "Kanye."

06:04.197 --> 06:05.448
He comes up a lot,
doesn't he?

06:05.448 --> 06:07.117
So, I jammed a lot on here,

06:07.117 --> 06:09.828
and I accidentally
omitted "bathroom."

06:09.828 --> 06:14.207
So maybe "Hells yeah, bitch"
can mean that, as well?

06:14.207 --> 06:15.667
What's wrong?

06:15.667 --> 06:19.212
Is the board
an "epic fail"?

06:19.212 --> 06:20.755
Oh. What's that?

06:22.966 --> 06:25.051
Bonfire at Dragon's Cove.

06:25.051 --> 06:27.387
You can't get down there.

06:27.387 --> 06:28.597
Are you okay with that?

06:30.599 --> 06:33.393
♪♪

06:37.314 --> 06:38.732
Mom, this is trash.

06:38.732 --> 06:39.649
This goes here.

06:39.649 --> 06:42.652
♪♪

06:46.281 --> 06:47.324
Hey.

06:47.324 --> 06:49.284
Mrs. DiMeo,
what brings you here?

06:49.284 --> 06:51.328
Nothing, really.
Just righting the world.

06:51.328 --> 06:53.204
Miller:
<i>Good morning, students!</i>

06:53.204 --> 06:54.873
Oh, it's Homecoming Week,

06:54.873 --> 06:57.959
and Friday night, we're gonna
stomp all over Eastlake!

06:57.959 --> 06:59.628
[ Students cheering ]

06:59.628 --> 07:02.881
But first, I know all you
juniors and seniors are excited

07:02.881 --> 07:04.215
about tonight's bonfire!

07:04.215 --> 07:05.717
[ Students cheering ]

07:05.717 --> 07:07.510
I also know
you're all committed

07:07.510 --> 07:09.387
to making Lafayette
an inclusive school

07:09.387 --> 07:10.930
in which everyone
is treated equally.

07:10.930 --> 07:12.682
[ Students cheering ]

07:12.682 --> 07:14.267
Which is why,
out of sensitivity

07:14.267 --> 07:16.144
to a student
who I will not name,

07:16.144 --> 07:19.773
the beach bonfire
has been canceled.

07:19.773 --> 07:20.774
Boy: What'd she say?

07:20.774 --> 07:22.859
Girl: Come on!

07:22.859 --> 07:24.944
Uh, did everyone cheer
for that last part?
I couldn't hear.

07:29.323 --> 07:30.199
What did you do,
Mrs. DiMeo?

07:30.199 --> 07:31.617
The only thing
I could do.

07:31.617 --> 07:35.329
You seemed so sad because
everyone could go but you.

07:35.329 --> 07:41.460
"I didn't E‐X‐pect you to cancel
Kylie Jenner," I mean "it."

07:41.460 --> 07:42.586
I hate this new board.

07:42.586 --> 07:44.129
I don't know why
it's such a big deal.

07:44.129 --> 07:45.798
Back at
your old special‐ed schools,

07:45.798 --> 07:47.257
I got things canceled
all the time.

07:47.257 --> 07:49.259
All the moms did.
We took turns.

07:49.259 --> 07:51.136
Blind mom
canceled movie night.

07:51.136 --> 07:53.222
Deaf mom
canceled jazz band.

07:53.222 --> 07:55.182
There were never any events,
and everyone was happy.

07:57.476 --> 08:01.563
Well, you know, if you're upset
I got it canceled, I'll fix it.

08:01.563 --> 08:02.898
No, no!
You don't have to.

08:02.898 --> 08:05.359
Bryan Keefer's about to break up
with his girlfriend!

08:05.359 --> 08:07.653
That'll distract everyone!

08:07.653 --> 08:09.363
How do I know?

08:09.363 --> 08:10.739
How do you <i>not</i> know?

08:10.739 --> 08:13.242
[ Chuckles ] He barely even
looks at her anymore.

08:13.242 --> 08:14.993
Come on, ladies! Come on,
come on, come on, come on!

08:14.993 --> 08:16.620
[ Stopwatch beeps ]

08:16.620 --> 08:17.996
[ Sighs ]

08:21.792 --> 08:23.419
DiMeo, what gives?

08:23.419 --> 08:26.130
Yeah, you're so off, Dylan.
No trash talk?

08:26.130 --> 08:28.298
You didn't spit at any of us.
What happened?

08:28.298 --> 08:29.758
We're worried about you.

08:29.758 --> 08:31.427
I'm really sorry, guys.

08:31.427 --> 08:34.388
It's just... my world collapsed
today, literally.

08:34.388 --> 08:36.598
That means, like,
"a lot," right?
Yep.

08:36.598 --> 08:38.392
I mean, I thought I ran
because I loved it,

08:38.392 --> 08:39.435
but it turns out I don't.

08:39.435 --> 08:42.855
I do it
because my brother can't.

08:42.855 --> 08:44.064
Why do you guys run?

08:44.064 --> 08:47.651
Why?
Because it's fun.

08:47.651 --> 08:49.236
I mean,
I guess on some level

08:49.236 --> 08:50.904
it's because my dad's
an Olympic runner.

08:50.904 --> 08:52.573
And since the divorce,

08:52.573 --> 08:55.367
the only time I see him
is when he comes to my meets.

08:55.367 --> 08:56.452
Maybe.

08:56.452 --> 08:58.954
Girl: I definitely run
because it's fun.

08:58.954 --> 09:00.414
Of course, when I was 5,

09:00.414 --> 09:02.916
I did fall into the lion habitat
at the zoo.

09:02.916 --> 09:07.087
And every night in my dreams,
the lions chase me and eat me.

09:07.087 --> 09:09.173
So it's more the lions
than the fun.

09:09.173 --> 09:10.466
I think so, yeah.

09:10.466 --> 09:12.009
Yeah,
it's more the lions.

09:12.009 --> 09:13.594
Girl #2:
I run for the feeling.

09:13.594 --> 09:15.429
It's pain.

09:15.429 --> 09:17.973
But I deserve it.

09:17.973 --> 09:20.476
For what I did.

09:20.476 --> 09:22.895
Yikes.

09:22.895 --> 09:24.438
[ Sighs ]

09:24.438 --> 09:26.356
I never wanted
to be a coach.

09:26.356 --> 09:29.026
And I also never wanted
to raise a child that's
obviously not mine.

09:29.026 --> 09:30.444
And this beard?

09:30.444 --> 09:32.196
Total cry for help,
thanks for noticing.

09:34.865 --> 09:36.575
All right, bye.

09:39.119 --> 09:40.913
Hey, Ray.

09:40.913 --> 09:43.415
Our garbage
is in the garbage.

09:43.415 --> 09:45.876
Ha ha. But wait...

09:45.876 --> 09:47.961
there's more.

09:47.961 --> 09:50.881
♪♪

09:50.881 --> 09:53.175
You did this?

09:53.175 --> 09:56.720
Well, yeah.
I saw you with that girl.

09:56.720 --> 09:59.890
I don't get this whole
"caring what other
people think" thing,

09:59.890 --> 10:01.892
but I asked myself,
"What's more important?

10:01.892 --> 10:04.520
My son or my love
of other people's trash?"

10:04.520 --> 10:05.771
And I won.

10:05.771 --> 10:07.731
Was it close?
Doesn't matter.

10:07.731 --> 10:09.691
Thank you so much.

10:09.691 --> 10:11.693
Well, what are you gonna do
with all that old junk?

10:11.693 --> 10:13.487
[ Crunching ]

10:13.487 --> 10:15.697
Ray: We're putting garbage
in the garbage truck,

10:15.697 --> 10:17.699
not taking it out.

10:17.699 --> 10:19.618
This is
a dream come true.

10:19.618 --> 10:20.828
Jimmy: Yep.

10:20.828 --> 10:23.163
Also, dream bigger.

10:23.163 --> 10:26.834
♪♪

10:26.834 --> 10:31.255
Welcome to the new, improved,
inclusive Homecoming Bonfire!

10:31.255 --> 10:32.589
Whoo‐hoo!

10:32.589 --> 10:34.967
So grab a snack
and hang 10 ‐‐

10:34.967 --> 10:37.386
or however many you can hang ‐‐

10:37.386 --> 10:39.888
and let's party!

10:39.888 --> 10:41.890
Fire‐master,
go light the bonfire.

10:41.890 --> 10:43.475
[ Switch clicking ]

10:43.475 --> 10:45.811
Damn it!

10:45.811 --> 10:49.022
[ Switch clicks ]

10:49.022 --> 10:51.024
Great.
It even sucks when it's working.

10:58.490 --> 10:59.992
Hello, darling.

10:59.992 --> 11:02.786
What is <i>this?</i>

11:02.786 --> 11:05.706
I promised my son
this bonfire would be
more fun than the original.

11:05.706 --> 11:07.249
Where's the debauchery?

11:07.249 --> 11:09.334
Where's
the sexual tension?

11:09.334 --> 11:13.380
The stench of teenage hormones
should be overpowering!

11:13.380 --> 11:15.507
We have badminton.

11:15.507 --> 11:19.678
You better figure out
a way to make this party fun.

11:19.678 --> 11:21.221
Without alcohol.

11:21.221 --> 11:23.223
[ Whispering ]
Get them alcohol!

11:25.475 --> 11:30.355
Okay, beach bums,
who's ready to limbo?

11:30.355 --> 11:31.899
Wait. No, no, no!
You can't leave.

11:31.899 --> 11:33.567
I mean, this whole party
is for you.

11:33.567 --> 11:36.361
"This is a disaster."

11:36.361 --> 11:37.779
You're right.

11:37.779 --> 11:41.408
I'm sensing a lot of unspoken
thoughts, squelched emotions...

11:41.408 --> 11:42.951
Uh...
Oh, my God.

11:42.951 --> 11:44.119
It's so obvious.

11:44.119 --> 11:45.996
We need to have
a rap session.

11:45.996 --> 11:47.289
No.
Yes!

11:47.289 --> 11:48.957
What are you doing?

11:48.957 --> 11:50.584
I am texting Jillian

11:50.584 --> 11:53.086
to tell her that she is welcome
to come to the house anytime

11:53.086 --> 11:54.296
to check out my probe.

11:54.296 --> 11:55.756
[ Chuckles ]

11:59.259 --> 12:01.345
You know, I'm so happy.

12:01.345 --> 12:03.513
This is a new chapter
in our lives ‐‐

12:03.513 --> 12:05.390
a fresh start
with no junk.

12:05.390 --> 12:08.143
Oh, you got to be
kidding me.

12:08.143 --> 12:09.186
What?

12:09.186 --> 12:12.648
Check out that lamp.

12:12.648 --> 12:15.192
Should I stop?

12:15.192 --> 12:17.236
No.

12:17.236 --> 12:19.696
I don't care how beautiful
it is, it's trash.

12:19.696 --> 12:20.739
Son, you need to see
something.

12:20.739 --> 12:22.616
There's two.

12:22.616 --> 12:24.243
It's a set?

12:24.243 --> 12:26.078
When is this
gonna happen again?

12:26.078 --> 12:30.332
Your love of matching furniture,
my love of trash.

12:30.332 --> 12:31.792
One last score,
then we go straight?

12:31.792 --> 12:33.961
♪♪

12:36.296 --> 12:38.882
Let's do it.
Let's do it!

12:38.882 --> 12:42.052
Okay, Lafayette, you know
how these rap sessions go.

12:42.052 --> 12:46.598
Who wants to give voice to their
frustration about this event?

12:46.598 --> 12:49.226
I think I just feel ‐‐
Let's start with a student,
Richard.

12:49.226 --> 12:50.435
Oh, okay.
Mm‐hmm.

12:50.435 --> 12:53.021
Uh, I just think
it's kind of unfortunate

12:53.021 --> 12:55.148
that the best activity
of the year

12:55.148 --> 12:57.276
got ruined to accommodate
one student.

12:57.276 --> 12:58.944
Well, he didn't want
to cancel it.

12:58.944 --> 13:01.154
Kenneth, we don't attack,
we listen.

13:01.154 --> 13:04.074
Thank you, Kayla.
Who else feels this way?

13:04.074 --> 13:06.618
Yes, Tommy.

13:06.618 --> 13:09.538
I put my blood, sweat, and tears
into playing football

13:09.538 --> 13:11.957
so that I can go to
events like the bonfire

13:11.957 --> 13:13.542
and hook up
with any girl I want.

13:13.542 --> 13:16.336
So when that gets taken away,
it's not fair to me.

13:16.336 --> 13:18.505
Or to any girl I want.

13:18.505 --> 13:20.507
I hear you.
Let it out.

13:20.507 --> 13:23.093
Now I'm gonna be all horny
during the game.

13:23.093 --> 13:24.052
Not sure
that was worth mentioning.

13:24.052 --> 13:25.220
Next?

13:25.220 --> 13:27.180
Zach:
Look, no one's mad at JJ.

13:27.180 --> 13:29.474
He just wants to have
the same high school experience

13:29.474 --> 13:31.059
as the rest of us.
Dude's a class act.

13:31.059 --> 13:33.520
But if anyone else got it
canceled, we'd be mad at them.

13:33.520 --> 13:36.523
So isn't it demeaning to JJ
to <i>not</i> blame him?

13:36.523 --> 13:38.191
Holy crap,
that's evolved.

13:38.191 --> 13:39.693
Girl: Yeah, he's right.

13:39.693 --> 13:41.194
We should respect JJ
as our equal

13:41.194 --> 13:42.154
and be mad at him.

13:42.154 --> 13:44.239
Mm‐hmm.
That is right.

13:44.239 --> 13:48.326
And in that spirit of respect,
what might you say to him?

13:48.326 --> 13:49.995
"Screw you for ruining
everything"?

13:49.995 --> 13:52.205
That's good.
It's not that good.

13:52.205 --> 13:53.540
Zach: "For someone
who doesn't walk,

13:53.540 --> 13:55.125
you sure do trample
on our rights."

13:55.125 --> 13:56.168
So articulate.

13:56.168 --> 13:58.670
How is your homework
always so bad?

13:58.670 --> 14:01.923
"Your mom might be hot,
but your behavior's not."

14:01.923 --> 14:02.966
Kind of
an interesting subplot.

14:02.966 --> 14:05.218
I am so proud
of all of you.

14:05.218 --> 14:07.345
Only Lafayette
would care about JJ enough

14:07.345 --> 14:09.389
to tell him
how much we resent him.

14:09.389 --> 14:12.142
Let's just give ourselves
a hand.
Yeah.

14:12.142 --> 14:14.352
Great job.
[ Cheers and applause ]

14:14.352 --> 14:16.646
Enough!

14:16.646 --> 14:18.023
Enough!

14:18.023 --> 14:20.067
I thought you guys were cool.

14:20.067 --> 14:21.318
Dakota?

14:21.318 --> 14:22.486
Kaden?

14:22.486 --> 14:23.487
Hayden?

14:23.487 --> 14:24.780
Jaden?

14:24.780 --> 14:26.531
Wow,
that's a lot of ‐aden names.

14:26.531 --> 14:28.033
Geez. Where was I?

14:28.033 --> 14:29.826
Oh, yeah.
Screw all of you!

14:29.826 --> 14:31.161
And your names!

14:31.161 --> 14:32.037
[ Gasps ]

14:32.037 --> 14:34.498
Come on, JJ!

14:34.498 --> 14:38.043
Yes, I will take a s'more for me
and for JJ, thank you.

14:38.043 --> 14:40.003
Come on, JJ!

14:40.003 --> 14:41.922
Who would
throw this away?

14:41.922 --> 14:44.174
It's a crazy world
we live in, son.

14:44.174 --> 14:45.717
Look in this bag.

14:45.717 --> 14:47.677
A whisk, a throw pillow?

14:47.677 --> 14:49.346
Is that a trivet?

14:49.346 --> 14:51.306
No, it's <i>our</i> trivet.

14:51.306 --> 14:53.141
In the van!

14:53.141 --> 14:56.186
♪♪

15:00.190 --> 15:02.984
Young woman: [ Screams ]
Where'd it go?

15:02.984 --> 15:04.528
Mom, someone just stole

15:04.528 --> 15:08.657
everything
I was gonna take to college!

15:08.657 --> 15:10.283
Drive! Drive!

15:15.372 --> 15:17.457
Oh, my God. Oh, my God!
We got to take it back.

15:17.457 --> 15:19.668
What are we gonna say?
This is so humiliating!

15:19.668 --> 15:21.294
Eh, I'll do it.

15:21.294 --> 15:23.713
Seriously?!
How are you okay with this?!

15:23.713 --> 15:27.092
Nothing this insane family does
gives you panic attacks.

15:27.092 --> 15:28.927
I have
high blood pressure!

15:28.927 --> 15:31.721
I am 13,
and I had to give up pickles!

15:31.721 --> 15:35.308
I love pickles!
Pickles are great.

15:35.308 --> 15:38.186
Buddy, why do you care so much
what other people think?

15:38.186 --> 15:39.396
Why don't you?

15:39.396 --> 15:42.065
Seriously, Dad,
don't you want to be normal?

15:42.065 --> 15:44.151
How can you
live like this?
[ Brakes squeal ]

15:47.487 --> 15:48.864
You want to know how?

15:48.864 --> 15:50.740
Because all this stuff,

15:50.740 --> 15:52.993
other people's opinions,

15:52.993 --> 15:55.328
it's nothing.

15:55.328 --> 15:57.038
You know
what's <i>not</i> nothing?

15:57.038 --> 15:59.791
A doctor tells you there's
something wrong with your kid,

15:59.791 --> 16:02.043
all the things
he's never gonna do,

16:02.043 --> 16:05.839
and it's
a nice, long list.

16:05.839 --> 16:08.341
But look at your brother.

16:08.341 --> 16:10.760
He's great.
He's smart, funny.

16:10.760 --> 16:12.387
Without naming names,

16:12.387 --> 16:14.973
he's apparently cooler
than some of my other kids.

16:14.973 --> 16:18.226
So now when something happens,
it's like, "What else you got?

16:18.226 --> 16:20.020
Bring it on."

16:20.020 --> 16:22.397
I get it ‐‐
normal seems good.

16:22.397 --> 16:24.399
But guess what ‐‐
we're not normal.

16:24.399 --> 16:26.818
We're better.
We're...

16:26.818 --> 16:28.612
bulletproof.

16:28.612 --> 16:31.406
♪♪

16:36.161 --> 16:37.078
What are you doing?

16:37.078 --> 16:39.497
I'm taking the stuff back.

16:39.497 --> 16:42.876
I got it, Dad.
I'm bulletproof, too.

16:45.962 --> 16:47.172
Did it get better?

16:47.172 --> 16:48.423
Yeah, it was great.

16:48.423 --> 16:50.383
Everyone put JJ
on their shoulders,

16:50.383 --> 16:52.719
and they did a conga line.
Oh, really?

16:52.719 --> 16:55.305
You're gonna have to learn that
that's my sarcastic voice.

16:55.305 --> 16:56.890
This is all their fault.

16:56.890 --> 17:00.185
That was the worst alternative
bonfire I have ever been to.

17:00.185 --> 17:01.895
You've been
to alternative bonfires?

17:01.895 --> 17:03.271
Anything
that isn't a bonfire

17:03.271 --> 17:04.606
is an alternative
to a bonfire, Kenneth.

17:06.691 --> 17:07.734
I tried.

17:07.734 --> 17:10.070
I mean, what could I have done
differently?

17:10.070 --> 17:13.031
Look, I know this thing of ours
is in its early stages,

17:13.031 --> 17:16.660
but am I allowed to answer
really obvious questions?

17:16.660 --> 17:18.620
Consider this
a test case.

17:18.620 --> 17:21.831
I see the way that you fight for
this guy, and it's beautiful.

17:21.831 --> 17:23.959
But he's in
a plain, old high school now.

17:23.959 --> 17:26.711
And a mom,
even an amazing one,

17:26.711 --> 17:29.047
she can't be the one
fixing everything.

17:29.047 --> 17:32.884
Well, maybe
you have a point.

17:32.884 --> 17:36.263
You do seem to be a bit
of an expert on high school.

17:36.263 --> 17:38.306
Well, you know...
Really not a compliment.

17:40.809 --> 17:42.018
Good night, buddy.

17:46.314 --> 17:49.401
[ Door opens, closes ]

17:49.401 --> 17:53.113
I'm sorry I made it
harder for you.

17:53.113 --> 17:56.741
"Can I, uh,
tell you something?"

17:56.741 --> 17:58.952
Anything.

17:58.952 --> 18:03.707
"I wanted you to help."

18:03.707 --> 18:05.667
Really?

18:05.667 --> 18:07.460
So it's not just me
who doesn't know how to do this?

18:07.460 --> 18:10.797
Mm. Good.

18:10.797 --> 18:12.299
All right, we'll ‐‐

18:12.299 --> 18:16.469
we'll figure it out together ‐‐
separately.

18:16.469 --> 18:20.932
And I know you'll get
those friends back.

18:20.932 --> 18:22.517
Oh, stop!

18:22.517 --> 18:24.811
Don't give me that look
that makes me do things.

18:29.566 --> 18:31.901
Oh, my God!
You found my things!

18:31.901 --> 18:33.862
I didn't find them.

18:33.862 --> 18:34.863
I took them.

18:34.863 --> 18:36.489
What? Why?

18:36.489 --> 18:38.450
Because I thought
they were garbage.

18:38.450 --> 18:42.037
Sis, what's going on?
Hey, do I know you?

18:42.037 --> 18:44.414
Yeah.
You're friends with...

18:44.414 --> 18:45.540
Ray?

18:45.540 --> 18:48.126
Hey, Jillian.

18:48.126 --> 18:50.462
Hey, every girl
in my grade.

18:50.462 --> 18:51.963
<i>He</i> took my stuff.

18:51.963 --> 18:55.133
But it's okay, because
he thought it was garbage.

18:55.133 --> 18:57.135
And why were you
taking my garbage?

18:57.135 --> 18:59.929
Because I'm bulletproof?

18:59.929 --> 19:04.059
[ Laughing ] Okay!
Ah. Yeah.

19:04.059 --> 19:06.061
That shame thing,
I'm ‐‐ I'm getting it.

19:10.273 --> 19:13.151
Morning ‐‐ almost.
Again.

19:13.151 --> 19:14.611
I know I said
I wouldn't help you anymore,

19:14.611 --> 19:16.946
but I had an idea about
how to get all your friends back

19:16.946 --> 19:18.073
in a split second.

19:18.073 --> 19:19.616
And then I will never
help you again.

19:19.616 --> 19:22.035
You know, you can rot
in the street for all I care.

19:22.035 --> 19:23.328
Are you game?

19:23.328 --> 19:24.079
Yes, okay.

19:24.079 --> 19:25.830
The best part of this is,

19:25.830 --> 19:27.666
Mom will have done
nothing at all.

19:27.666 --> 19:30.335
Eastlake will.

19:30.335 --> 19:33.880
It's a big swing, but I decided
I'd do this with any of my kids.

19:33.880 --> 19:36.424
Right.
Give it a go.

19:36.424 --> 19:37.550
[ Wheelchair motor whirs,
chains clank ]

19:37.550 --> 19:39.302
Fantastic.

19:39.302 --> 19:41.888
You know, I figured

19:41.888 --> 19:46.142
there's nothing I like to do
more than fight for you.

19:46.142 --> 19:47.602
Let's give your friends
a taste.

19:47.602 --> 19:51.022
Okay, I'm gonna hide this key
way back ‐‐

19:51.022 --> 19:52.232
Oh, they look stupid.

19:52.232 --> 19:54.776
I'll leave it
right there.

19:55.944 --> 19:57.821
Is that JJ DiMeo?

19:57.821 --> 19:58.738
‐Dude!
‐Dude!

19:58.738 --> 19:59.656
‐Dude!
‐Dude!

19:59.656 --> 20:01.199
‐Dude!
‐Dude, are you okay?

20:01.199 --> 20:03.243
Eastlake did this to you?
Not cool!

20:03.243 --> 20:04.285
JJ's our boy!

20:04.285 --> 20:05.870
You guys unlock him.

20:05.870 --> 20:07.372
I'll go to his house
and tell his mom.

20:07.372 --> 20:08.581
♪♪

20:08.581 --> 20:09.874
Hey, what's this for?

20:09.874 --> 20:13.378
Hey, Eastlake,
you forgot your key!

20:13.378 --> 20:15.338
Oh, my God.

20:15.338 --> 20:19.134
All right, come on.

20:19.134 --> 20:20.427
You're gonna pay for this,
Eastlake!

20:20.427 --> 20:25.098
[ Players grunting ]

20:25.098 --> 20:27.016
♪ When it's on, it's on ♪

20:27.016 --> 20:28.351
♪ Let's get it on ♪

20:28.351 --> 20:30.729
I don't know who JJ is,
but I'm sorry!

20:30.729 --> 20:32.689
♪ Come on, now ♪

20:32.689 --> 20:34.357
[ Cheering ]

20:36.860 --> 20:38.027
[ Whistle blows ]

20:38.027 --> 20:39.738
No call!

20:39.738 --> 20:41.614
I heard about
what you did to that kid.

20:41.614 --> 20:42.866
[ Cheers and applause ]

20:42.866 --> 20:45.034
This is all for you, JJ!

20:45.034 --> 20:46.369
Whoo!
[ Whistle blows ]

20:46.369 --> 20:48.747
Does everyone who plays a sport
do it for JJ?

20:48.747 --> 20:50.498
Did we get the one
that locked you up, JJ?

20:50.498 --> 20:51.791
No, not yet.

20:51.791 --> 20:52.751
Shut up, shut up.

20:52.751 --> 20:56.421
♪♪

20:56.421 --> 20:58.590
Are we okay
with all this carnage?

20:58.590 --> 21:02.719
Oh, yeah, yeah.
Go, American football! Go on!

21:02.719 --> 21:04.471
You having
a good time, JJ?

21:04.471 --> 21:07.098
"Hells yeah, bitch."

21:07.098 --> 21:08.725
Is that ‐‐
That's new.

21:08.725 --> 21:10.602
Oh! That means
he has to go to the bathroom.

21:10.602 --> 21:12.061
Get up. Go on.
Get up. Go on.

21:12.061 --> 21:13.021
Sorry, darling.
Yeah, go on.
